{
  "text": "Three auxiliary detectors on the CTIO summit, supplied by DES, provide information for photometric calibration. An All-Sky Radiometric Camera (RASICAM) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] ] is used to monitor the sky using the wavelength range 970 nm < \u03bb<1250 nm. In this wavelength range, relatively warm clouds are easily distinguished from cold, clear skies. \"GPSMon\" [CITATION_4] 10] provides a cross-check of the amount of precipitable water vapor (PWV) in the atmosphere. The Atmospheric Transmission Monitoring Camera (aTmCam) [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] was tested in Y1 and Y2 and operated consistently starting at the beginning of Y2. The aTmCam consists of a Paramount telescope mount and four small telescopes, each with a different narrowband filter, which monitors the brightness of suitable standard stars, thus providing the atmospheric transmission in wavelength regions dominated by the PWV and aerosol optical depth.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "56045879",
